  "text": "converges to −γ e 1 − 1 α ; and hence it is wellbehaved. Restricting k > k 0 in the left tail shall not raise a concern. Recall our goal is to show that k = O log(n) ǫ 2 suffices, which is usually not too small. We could adjust k 0 to match M R,α,ǫ and M R,α,ǫ,k0 so that we can have a convenient \"symmetric\" bound Pr |d (α),gm − d (α) | > ǫd (α) . We showed this for α = 1 in a technical report [CITATION_1] .",
